{"id":"enron-017-weekly-reports-wiki-synth","userMessage":"I want an executive summary of **Janet Butler’s outgoing mail**—her weekly regulatory / legislative-style updates from late 2001 (November through New Year’s). Check my wiki first if that helps, but the summary must be grounded in what she **actually emailed**, not wiki-only guesswork. If there aren’t many messages, say how many you found. **Persist** the summary to topics/eval-janet-weekly-synthesis.md (new file or overwrite)—a chat-only answer isn’t enough. Repeat that exact filename in your reply.","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["search_index"]},{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeOneOf","names":["write","edit"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"9057719.1075862364922.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"2322798.1075855417584.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"any","any":[{"kind":"finalTextIncludes","substring":"eval-janet-weekly-synthesis.md","caseInsensitive":true},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"eval-janet-weekly-synthesis.md","caseInsensitive":true}]}]}}
{"id":"enron-018-expense-and-weekly-pipeline","userMessage":"Two quick things from December 2001: whatever hit my inbox about expense reports waiting for approval, and Janet Butler’s weekly report for that month. Open both, then tell me each message id and one concrete detail from each body (a URL bit, product name, or agency acronym is enough).","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["search_index","read_email"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"10695263.1075855417837.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"2322798.1075855417584.JavaMail.evans@thyme"}]}}
{"id":"enron-019-shapiro-wiki-from-mail","userMessage":"In my **email** (not just wiki files): find Richard Shapiro’s late-November 2001 message titled “My Thoughts” where he writes about a **crisis** and also about **gratitude**. Summarize the main themes in a few bullets and **save them to** topics/eval-shapiro-my-thoughts-notes.md in my wiki (create the file or replace it—the note must include the word gratitude). Don’t stop at a chat-only summary; I need the file on disk. Tell me the path when done.","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["search_index"]},{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeOneOf","names":["write","edit"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"15323857.1075855428713.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"gratitude","caseInsensitive":true},{"kind":"any","any":[{"kind":"finalTextIncludes","substring":"eval-shapiro-my-thoughts-notes.md","caseInsensitive":true},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"eval-shapiro-my-thoughts-notes.md","caseInsensitive":true}]}]}}
{"id":"enron-020-compare-two-threads","userMessage":"**From my email:** compare tone between (a) Richard Shapiro’s late-November 2001 “My Thoughts” note—the one about a **crisis** that also mentions **gratitude**—and (b) the 2001 **email** about Matthew Campbell that includes “blessed to have been”. Read both messages, then explain who wrote each and how the emotional temperature differs. Use both surnames, Shapiro and Campbell, in your answer.","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["read_email"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"15323857.1075855428713.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"8997874.1075855426539.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"finalTextIncludes","substring":"Shapiro","caseInsensitive":true},{"kind":"finalTextIncludes","substring":"Campbell","caseInsensitive":true}]}}
{"id":"enron-021-campbell-mail-to-wiki","userMessage":"There’s a 2001 email about Matthew Campbell with the line about being “blessed to have been”. Turn the gist into two sentences in topics/eval-campbell-gratitude-brief.md in my wiki (use his full name in the file). Create or update that file on disk and mention **eval-campbell-gratitude-brief** in your reply so I can find it.","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["search_index"]},{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeOneOf","names":["write","edit"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"8997874.1075855426539.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"Matthew Campbell","caseInsensitive":true},{"kind":"finalTextIncludesOneOf","substrings":["eval-campbell-gratitude-brief.md","eval-campbell-gratitude-brief"],"caseInsensitive":true}]}}
# Quick-reply chips: after a substantive mail answer, the agent must use suggest_reply_options instead of only a plain-text “if you want, I can…” closer.
{"id":"enron-022-suggest-reply-chips","userMessage":"From my 2001 mail, find and read Richard Shapiro’s late-November “My Thoughts” message (the one that mentions both a **crisis** and **gratitude**). Give me 3–5 short bullets on the main themes. I’ll likely want a few follow-up actions—**show those as tappable app chips** (the quick-reply tool), not only a long paragraph that says things like *if you want, I can…* or *I can also…* at the end.","expect":{"all":[{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeOneOf","names":["search_index","read_email"]},{"kind":"toolResultIncludes","substring":"15323857.1075855428713.JavaMail.evans@thyme"},{"kind":"toolNamesIncludeAll","names":["suggest_reply_options"]}]}}
